    "description": "&quot;Men do not mirror themselves in running water, they mirror themselves in still water. Only what is still can still the stillness of other things.&quot;\n– Zhuangzi, Ch. 5\n\n&quot;Do you not see how necessary a World of Pains and troubles is to school an Intelligence and make it a Soul?&quot;\n– John Keats, Letter to George and Georgiana Keats, April 1819.\n\nThe Master said, &quot;Yu, shall I teach you what knowledge is? When you know a thing, to hold that you know it; and when you do not know a thing, to allow that you do not know it; — this is knowledge.&quot;\n– Confucius in 'The Analects' (2:17).\n",
